---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import OrnamentalDivider from '../components/OrnamentalDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What Alone in the Dungeon is, and who is rolling the dice."
>
  <section class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-10 text-center">
    <h1 class="font-pixel text-4xl text-glow-50 md:text-5xl">About</h1>
    <OrnamentalDivider class="mx-auto mt-10 w-44 text-violet-500" />
  </section>

  <div class="prose-body mx-auto max-w-[var(--container-prose)] px-6 pb-16">
    <p>
      <strong>Alone in the Dungeon</strong> is my journal, hobby log, and live play archive of my journey through solo roleplaying. I will also feature some solo friendly wargame coverage, tips on how you can jump into the world of solo tabletop gaming, and the narrative stories that come from doing so. I also believe that TTRPG are a form of self transformation and hopefully, self development and improvement. I want to share my experiences with you.
    </p>

    <p>
     Matt Gilbert is Alone in the Dungeon. I am husband, father of four, artist, fledgling author, and apparently a miniaturist. Whatever that means. I'm just here having fun with it. I also run a daily hobby vlog and indie tabletop related youtube channel / website called <a href="https://hobbinomicon.com">The Hobbinomicon</a>.
     You can check out all my projects by visiting <a href="https://mattglbrt.com">mattglbrt.com</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
    I also sell 3d printed and resin cast miniatures that I do all by myself over at <a href="https://yellowimp.com">Yellow Imp Miniatures</a>. Original sculpts from me coming soon.
    </p>

    <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/live-plays/">Live Plays</a></strong> — Raw recordings and actual play sessions of playing solo ttrpgs.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/reviews/">Reviews</a></strong> — honest takes on games, rulebooks, and hobby products.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/stories/">Stories</a></strong> — curated stories derived from my actual plays, with the mechanics stripped away. Inspired by <a href="https://www.taleofthemanticore.com/"><em>Tales of the Manticore</em>.</a></li>
      <li><strong><a href="/hobby/">Hobby</a></strong> — completed miniature projects, terrain, painting guides, and step-by-step hobby guides.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/guides/">Guides</a></strong> — reading lists, Appendix N indexes, and reference guides for solo play.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/news/">News</a></strong> — industry news, releases, jams, and other cool things worth a look.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
